122
00:07:20.916 --> 00:07:23.936
and we know that these extracellular vesicles are

123
00:07:24.636 --> 00:07:27.176
ubiquitously secreted by almost all cell types.

124
00:07:27.536 --> 00:07:29.096
They are evolutionarily conserved.

125
00:07:29.436 --> 00:07:30.096
They have

126
00:07:34.136 --> 00:07:36.156
overlapping and non-overlapping cargos.

127
00:07:36.736 --> 00:07:40.416
They range in size all the way from these nanometer-type structures

128
00:07:40.876 --> 00:07:44.756
to the micrometer-size vesicles, like microvesicles and

129
00:07:45.236 --> 00:07:45.896
oncosomes.

130
00:07:47.496 --> 00:07:47.876
And

131
00:07:49.236 --> 00:07:52.286
extracellular particles are a newer subpopulation,

132
00:07:53.176 --> 00:07:55.256
that lack membrane encapsulation.

133
00:07:55.676 --> 00:07:56.016
I think

134
00:07:57.616 --> 00:08:01.026
David Liden sort of pioneered this field with the discovery of

135
00:08:01.416 --> 00:08:05.116
exomeres. And Bob Coffey's lab later then identified

