144
00:08:31.256 --> 00:08:35.086
than 200 nanometers is referred to as the small EVs

145
00:08:35.216 --> 00:08:38.687
or the large EVs respectively. So these small EVs

146
00:08:39.476 --> 00:08:43.136
include the exosomes, like I just mentioned, these that are derived from

147
00:08:43.177 --> 00:08:46.856
multivesicular bodies. There are several ways in which

148
00:08:46.896 --> 00:08:49.356
cargos can be loaded into these vesicles.

149
00:08:50.036 --> 00:08:53.436
Two well-studied ones are shown here, but additional

150
00:08:53.476 --> 00:08:57.436
mechanisms also exist. So you have this ESCRT-mediated

151
00:08:57.476 --> 00:09:01.116
sorting of ubiquitinated cargo into these intraluminal

152
00:09:01.136 --> 00:09:04.836
vesicles. And then you also have this Alix and tenascin-R dependent

153
00:09:04.976 --> 00:09:08.556
pathway, which also is dependent on changes to the lipid

154
00:09:08.596 --> 00:09:12.216
membrane that allows the inclusion of cargos into these

155
00:09:12.256 --> 00:09:15.956
vesicles. These small vesicles, these small ectosomes that bud

156
00:09:15.996 --> 00:09:19.896
directly from the cell surface, also appear to require an ectosome

157
00:09:20.776 --> 00:09:21.636
ESCRT type

158
00:09:23.776 --> 00:09:26.956
machinery that's required for pinching from the cell surface.

159
00:09:26.976 --> 00:09:30.876
And ESCRT is this endosomal sorting complex required for transport.

160
00:09:30.916 --> 00:09:34.316
Now, the larger vesicles, on the other hand, are quite diverse.

161
00:09:35.796 --> 00:09:37.616
There's quite a few of them, as you can see here.

162
00:09:37.676 --> 00:09:41.636
There are microvesicles and oncosomes which form by the

163
00:09:41.676 --> 00:09:43.336
budding and pinching of the plasma membrane.

164
00:09:43.736 --> 00:09:47.516
There are these migrasomes that form on the retracting edge of the cell.

165
00:09:47.976 --> 00:09:51.496
And there's this midbody remnants that are formed from a

166
00:09:52.076 --> 00:09:55.476
post-cell division. And then the blebosome and

167
00:09:55.856 --> 00:09:58.016
variations of it. This is the largest one

168
00:09:59.656 --> 00:09:59.916
yet.

169
00:10:01.276 --> 00:10:05.246
And they all appear to require actin-myosin-based

170
00:10:05.316 --> 00:10:07.416
contractile forces for their release.

171
00:10:08.056 --> 00:10:11.676
But they may also have perhaps distinct

172
00:10:11.936 --> 00:10:14.816
biogenesis mechanisms, and that's something that is an

173
00:10:16.276 --> 00:10:19.156
active area of investigation in the field.

174
00:10:20.536 --> 00:10:23.916
So

175
00:10:24.656 --> 00:10:28.116
these EVs, I

176
00:10:28.176 --> 00:10:31.776
always think about them as functional units,

177
00:10:32.416 --> 00:10:34.636
where they may bring about cargo exchange,

178
00:10:35.436 --> 00:10:39.096
or signaling. They may contain molecules that serve as

179
00:10:39.116 --> 00:10:42.716
