266
00:15:45.332 --> 00:15:45.852
matrix.

267
00:15:47.082 --> 00:15:49.312
So the pinching of these

268
00:15:51.412 --> 00:15:55.372
microvesicles is dependent on changes in membrane phospholipids

269
00:15:55.412 --> 00:15:57.952
and also actin-myosin-based contractility.

270
00:15:58.652 --> 00:16:02.252
Both the Af6 and Rho proteins have been thought to facilitate

271
00:16:02.952 --> 00:16:06.512
this actin contractile force that's required

272
00:16:06.992 --> 00:16:10.682
for this budding. It's also accompanied by changes in

273
00:16:10.972 --> 00:16:14.842
membrane phospholipids. And so this mechanism of budding is

274
00:16:14.872 --> 00:16:18.232
quite different from what you would see with the small vesicles that

275
00:16:18.892 --> 00:16:20.372
pinch off from the cell surface and

276
00:16:21.292 --> 00:16:22.932
utilize the ESCRT machinery.

277
00:16:23.992 --> 00:16:26.772
Okay. The

278
00:16:28.152 --> 00:16:30.032
proteome, it has a very diverse proteasome.

279
00:16:30.072 --> 00:16:33.992
It also contains nucleic acids, both RNA and DNA, as is

280
00:16:34.032 --> 00:16:37.212
common for most of these EV subtypes.

281
00:16:37.742 --> 00:16:41.532
Which then led us to propose that perhaps these microvesicles that are

282
00:16:41.572 --> 00:16:45.472
forming at the cell surface are convergence points for multiple vesicular

283
00:16:45.572 --> 00:16:46.672
transport pathways.

284
00:16:47.772 --> 00:16:51.492
And what we noted in particular was that many of the

285
00:16:51.532 --> 00:16:55.072
proteins that regulated the formation of these vesicles

286
00:16:55.752 --> 00:16:55.952
were

287
00:16:57.432 --> 00:17:01.052
trafficked along this Af6 early endosomal recycling pathway.

288
00:17:01.552 --> 00:17:05.432
Which led us to hypothesize that perhaps Af6 regulated recycling

289
00:17:05.772 --> 00:17:09.432
was at least one particular mechanism by which cargos might be

290
00:17:09.472 --> 00:17:13.412
directed to these sites. And that's what I'm going to focus on for the rest of this

291
00:17:13.492 --> 00:17:16.312
presentation. So we find that these

292
00:17:17.892 --> 00:17:18.633
vesicles

293
00:17:20.133 --> 00:17:24.113
are shed from regions of high blebbing when tumor cells adopt

294
00:17:24.152 --> 00:17:27.902
this very amoeboid phenotype. And here you can

295
00:17:27.972 --> 00:17:31.672
actually see we were looking at how a protease might be delivered to those

296
00:17:31.732 --> 00:17:35.672
sites, and you can see that the protease, MT1-MMP

297
00:17:35.732 --> 00:17:38.952
localizes to these vesicles that are positive for the

298
00:17:39.692 --> 00:17:43.352
endosomal v-SNARE VAMP3 that sort of directs

299
00:17:43.412 --> 00:17:47.152
cargo to these sites. And there's very little overlap

300
00:17:47.172 --> 00:17:50.952
between this protease and this particular v-SNARE when

301
00:17:51.012 --> 00:17:54.292
cells are low blebbing and have this more spread or

302
00:17:54.352 --> 00:17:58.132
mesenchymal-like phenotype. What we went on to

303
00:17:58.192 --> 00:18:02.172
